The paper discusses a new gradient boosting toolkit that outperforms other publicly available boosting implementations in terms of quality on a variety of datasets. The paper focuses on two critical algorithmic advances introduced in CatBoost, which are the implementation of ordered boosting and an innovative algorithm for processing categorical features. These techniques were created to fight a prediction shift caused by a special kind of target leakage present in all currently existing implementations of gradient boosting algorithms. The paper's content is related to machine learning, artificial intelligence, computer vision, data science, and computational linguistics, which are all sub-categories of computer science. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS, and cs.CL.
